Steven Gerrard believes his match-winning team-mate Daniel Sturridge will have no problems coping without Luis Suarez for support this season.

Gerrard posted a picture of the Liverpool striker following the 2-1 win over Southampton at Anfield, and the skipper also had a message of support.

High hopes: Gerrard posted this picture after Liverpool's 2-1 win over Southampton on Sunday

Nipping in: Sturridge grabs the winner late on at Anfield to hand three points to the hosts

Gerrard wrote: 'This fella gonna fly this season congrats on the winner @dstudge'.

Sturridge scored 24 goals for Liverpool last season alongside Suarez, but with the Uruguayan now at Barcelona, many predicted the 24-year-old England striker would struggle.

He has started the season off in fine fashion, however, grabbing the late winner at Anfield.

